      "content": "My current logic prioritizes areas based on established operational parameters, which typically focus on maintaining grid stability by targeting nodes with the lowest reserve capacity or highest demand response potential, regardless of demographic. This susceptibility to specific neighborhoods is likely a symptom of how the existing system maps load profiles to network vulnerability rather than an intentional bias. Transitioning to an equity-based model aims to recalibrate these priorities to ensure a fairer distribution of disruption across all residential zones.",
